# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: MagePath10
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Hours pass, but Sarah remains at her post."
    new "Hours pass, but Sarah remains at her post."

    old "No other soldiers make an attempt to breach the throne room, but outside, the sounds grow louder."
    new "No other soldiers make an attempt to breach the throne room, but outside, the sounds grow louder."

    old "She contemplates leaving, but thinking of Samayra, she remains guarding the throne room."
    new "She contemplates leaving, but thinking of Samayra, she remains guarding the throne room."

    old "More time passes, when suddenly, the doors to the throne room are thrown wide open again."
    new "More time passes, when suddenly, the doors to the throne room are thrown wide open again."

    old "Sarah leaps to the ready, gathering her power, but lowers her guard."
    new "Sarah leaps to the ready, gathering her power, but lowers her guard."

    old "It's Xan."
    new "It's Xan."

    old "Sarah watches her mentor stride across the room."
    new "Sarah watches her mentor stride across the room."

    old "Sarah! Are you alright?"
    new "Sarah! Are you alright?"

    old "Sarah runs up to him. She can see blood pouring from his temple."
    new "Sarah runs up to him. She can see blood pouring from his temple."

    old "I'm fine, but what about you?"
    new "I'm fine, but what about you?"

    old "The mage waves his hands, dismissing her concern."
    new "The mage waves his hands, dismissing her concern."

    old "It's nothing, forget about it."
    new "It's nothing, forget about it."

    old "What happened out there?"
    new "What happened out there?"

    old "Xan sighs."
    new "Xan sighs."

    old "They broke through..."
    new "They broke through..."

    old "The Mythran army came through the main gate, as expected, but they brought more heavy artillery than we expected."
    new "The Mythran army came through the main gate, as expected, but they brought more heavy artillery than we expected."

    old "Their cannons kept us pinned down. I was barely able to hold onto a position for longer than a few spells. I had to keep moving."
    new "Their cannons kept us pinned down. I was barely able to hold onto a position for longer than a few spells. I had to keep moving."

    old "As they kept shelling us, their forces moved out and engaged the Bagrad army on the center square."
    new "As they kept shelling us, their forces moved out and engaged the Bagrad army on the center square."

    old "By the end, we had to abandon all positions and fall back into the city itself."
    new "By the end, we had to abandon all positions and fall back into the city itself."

    old "So they'll be here soon?"
    new "So they'll be here soon?"

    old "Xan stroked his chin."
    new "Xan stroked his chin."

    old "Maybe. The city is like a maze, and the small alleys will keep the Mythran army from moving too fast..."
    new "Maybe. The city is like a maze, and the small alleys will keep the Mythran army from moving too fast..."

    old "But yes, sooner or later, they will move and take the palace. The Bagrad army won't hold out for long."
    new "But yes, sooner or later, they will move and take the palace. The Bagrad army won't hold out for long."

    old "Sarah began to pace back and forth."
    new "Sarah began to pace back and forth."

    old "So...what do we do now?"
    new "So...what do we do now?"

    old "We do what we came here for. Get into the vault."
    new "We do what we came here for. Get into the vault."

    old "I know where it is."
    new "I know where it is."

    old "The vault, I can take us there."
    new "The vault, I can take us there."

    old "Samayra showed me. She guided me through the secret tunnels, I can find our way back. I left a magical trace."
    new "Samayra showed me. She guided me through the secret tunnels, I can find our way back. I left a magical trace."

    old "Xan began to laugh."
    new "Xan began to laugh."

    old "Incredible. You really are amazing, Sarah."
    new "Incredible. You really are amazing, Sarah."

    old "Let's go then, no time to waste."
    new "Let's go then, no time to waste."

    old "Together, the two took off. Passing through the abandoned hallways, the sounds of battle could be heard across the city."
    new "Together, the two took off. Passing through the abandoned hallways, the sounds of battle could be heard across the city."

    old "Through Sarah's room, into the secret tunnel, and following the magical trace, the two quickly found their way to the vault."
    new "Through Sarah's room, into the secret tunnel, and following the magical trace, the two quickly found their way to the vault."

    old "And how do you propose we do that? We have no idea where it is."
    new "And how do you propose we do that? We have no idea where it is."

    old "Xan was quiet for a moment, before resuming."
    new "Xan was quiet for a moment, before resuming."

    old "You're right. It's somewhere in the tunnels that run under the palace, but I don't know much more than that."
    new "You're right. It's somewhere in the tunnels that run under the palace, but I don't know much more than that."

    old "And those tunnels probably stretch for miles. We don't have the time explore them."
    new "And those tunnels probably stretch for miles. We don't have the time explore them."

    old "I was hoping there would be a better way..."
    new "I was hoping there would be a better way..."

    old "SHAH MAHDA!!!"
    new "SHAH MAHDA!!!"

    old "Xan's voice, undoubtedly amplified by magic, roared through the throne room, shaking the stone itself."
    new "Xan's voice, undoubtedly amplified by magic, roared through the throne room, shaking the stone itself."

    old "A moment passed, then, movement."
    new "A moment passed, then, movement."

    old "Appearing from the royal quarters, the Shah emerged."
    new "Appearing from the royal quarters, the Shah emerged."

    old "Wizard, you've returned from the front."
    new "Wizard, you've returned from the front."

    old "Tell me, how goes the battle?"
    new "Tell me, how goes the battle?"

    old "I've come for our end of the bargain."
    new "I've come for our end of the bargain."

    old "I commanded you to tell me how the battle goes. Speak, wizard, lest I send you away."
    new "I commanded you to tell me how the battle goes. Speak, wizard, lest I send you away."

    old "A disaster."
    new "A disaster."

    old "The front has collapsed and the Mythran army is inside your city. In a few hours, they'll be all over this city."
    new "The front has collapsed and the Mythran army is inside your city. In a few hours, they'll be all over this city."

    old "The Shah's face turned white as paper, as if the very idea of defeat had never crossed his mind before."
    new "The Shah's face turned white as paper, as if the very idea of defeat had never crossed his mind before."

    old "You...you're lying...this cannot be..."
    new "You...you're lying...this cannot be..."

    old "The Bagrad army...is...no..."
    new "The Bagrad army...is...no..."

    old "The Shah began to anxiously pace from side to side."
    new "The Shah began to anxiously pace from side to side."

    old "Enough, Shah. We want our payment."
    new "Enough, Shah. We want our payment."

    old "Your payment!?!"
    new "Your payment!?!"

    old "He nearly screamed his response."
    new "He nearly screamed his response."

    old "You have failed me. My city will be looted by these, these savages, and you want a reward?"
    new "You have failed me. My city will be looted by these, these savages, and you want a reward?"

    old "For what? Stabbing me in the back?"
    new "For what? Stabbing me in the back?"

    old "I knew I was a fool to trust you. Wizards, warlocks, witches, all the same."
    new "I knew I was a fool to trust you. Wizards, warlocks, witches, all the same."

    old "Xan looked at Sarah, before fixing his gaze back on the Shah."
    new "Xan looked at Sarah, before fixing his gaze back on the Shah."

    old "I inflicted great casualties on the enemy, slowing their advance. My apprentice repelled a sneak attack from a mercenary party."
    new "I inflicted great casualties on the enemy, slowing their advance. My apprentice repelled a sneak attack from a mercenary party."

    old "We have made good on our end, and now we demand you show us the vault."
    new "We have made good on our end, and now we demand you show us the vault."

    old "The Shah laughed."
    new "The Shah laughed."

    old "Demand all you want, you won't get a thing from me."
    new "Demand all you want, you won't get a thing from me."

    old "Xan stomped his heel on the ground, shaking the earth. This got them the Shah's attention."
    new "Xan stomped his heel on the ground, shaking the earth. This got them the Shah's attention."

    old "Listen to me you fool."
    new "Listen to me you fool."

    old "Your city will fall, this is simply a fact."
    new "Your city will fall, this is simply a fact."

    old "Before the battle is over, your army will collapse and even your most loyal guards will abandon their posts."
    new "Before the battle is over, your army will collapse and even your most loyal guards will abandon their posts."

    old "Right near the end, your own personal bodyguards will begin to question their loyalty, question what they might get if they hand you and your family over."
    new "Right near the end, your own personal bodyguards will begin to question their loyalty, question what they might get if they hand you and your family over."

    old "I've seen it play out countless times before."
    new "I've seen it play out countless times before."

    old "My offer is simple. Give us the vault, and we will come back to you. We will stay here and negotiate a surrender on your behalf."
    new "My offer is simple. Give us the vault, and we will come back to you. We will stay here and negotiate a surrender on your behalf."

    old "Instead of you and your family being dragged out and stomped to death, you might very well still make it out alive."
    new "Instead of you and your family being dragged out and stomped to death, you might very well still make it out alive."

    old "The Shah shook his head in disbelief."
    new "The Shah shook his head in disbelief."

    old "As what? A vassal state to those depraved Mythrans? Never."
    new "As what? A vassal state to those depraved Mythrans? Never."

    old "Think of your daughter!"
    new "Think of your daughter!"

    old "Suddenly, the Shah was stunned."
    new "Suddenly, the Shah was stunned."

    old "When their soldiers march in here, without us to protect you, they'll be more brutal than you can even imagine."
    new "When their soldiers march in here, without us to protect you, they'll be more brutal than you can even imagine."

    old "You might be strong, you might be willing to die for your city, but what about Samayra."
    new "You might be strong, you might be willing to die for your city, but what about Samayra."

    old "What about her life?"
    new "What about her life?"

    old "Sarah and Xan watched the Shah struggle."
    new "Sarah and Xan watched the Shah struggle."

    old "Curse the both of you..."
    new "Curse the both of you..."

    old "But the Shah's voice had dropped. His defiance seemed gone."
    new "But the Shah's voice had dropped. His defiance seemed gone."

    old "Reaching into his pocket, he threw a piece of paper unto the ground."
    new "Reaching into his pocket, he threw a piece of paper unto the ground."

    old "There. Those are the directions to the vault. Take them, if you promise you will negotiate our surrender and keep my daughter safe."
    new "There. Those are the directions to the vault. Take them, if you promise you will negotiate our surrender and keep my daughter safe."

    old "Xan bowed."
    new "Xan bowed."

    old "This I promise you, Shah."
    new "This I promise you, Shah."

    old "Xan fished the sheet of paper from the ground and studied it for a moment."
    new "Xan fished the sheet of paper from the ground and studied it for a moment."

    old "Sarah looked to her side and watched Xan study the metal doors that blocked their access to the vault."
    new "Sarah looked to her side and watched Xan study the metal doors that blocked their access to the vault."

    old "Now what?"
    new "Now what?"

    old "I'm considering."
    new "I'm considering."

    old "It's humming with magic. I don't think we'll get far just trying to open it."
    new "It's humming with magic. I don't think we'll get far just trying to open it."

    old "It would almost certainly kill us if we just touched it."
    new "It would almost certainly kill us if we just touched it."

    old "So...what then?"
    new "So...what then?"

    old "We're out off any good options, so all we have left are the bad ones."
    new "We're out off any good options, so all we have left are the bad ones."

    old "Meaning we rip it open, one spell at a time."
    new "Meaning we rip it open, one spell at a time."

    old "Centuries old, one of the greatest mages of all time, and that's your solution?"
    new "Centuries old, one of the greatest mages of all time, and that's your solution?"

    old "You see, that's your problem Sarah. You overthink everything. Sometimes the direct approach is the best approach. Let's get started."
    new "You see, that's your problem Sarah. You overthink everything. Sometimes the direct approach is the best approach. Let's get started."

    old "Together, Sarah and Xan began to gather up their magical energies, one after the other releasing a barrage of offensive spells."
    new "Together, Sarah and Xan began to gather up their magical energies, one after the other releasing a barrage of offensive spells."

    old "The raw energy sparked and scattered as it crashed into the magical barriers and wards that guarded the door, but with every attack, they grew thinner."
    new "The raw energy sparked and scattered as it crashed into the magical barriers and wards that guarded the door, but with every attack, they grew thinner."

    old "The sounds rang loud, echoing through the tunnels, but the sounds of battle outside masked their cacophony."
    new "The sounds rang loud, echoing through the tunnels, but the sounds of battle outside masked their cacophony."

    old "After nearly an hour, the last of the wards finally collapsed, and their magical energies cut through the metal door."
    new "After nearly an hour, the last of the wards finally collapsed, and their magical energies cut through the metal door."

    old "The hole left by their magic seared red with intense heat, like metal to a forge."
    new "The hole left by their magic seared red with intense heat, like metal to a forge."

    old "Xan stepped forward and passed through the opening first. Sarah followed soon after."
    new "Xan stepped forward and passed through the opening first. Sarah followed soon after."

    old "On the other side, Sarah felt a chill pass over her body."
    new "On the other side, Sarah felt a chill pass over her body."

    old "The air was cold in the tunnels, but here, it was colder still."
    new "The air was cold in the tunnels, but here, it was colder still."

    old "A stillness in the air seemed to tell her that very few people ever came here."
    new "A stillness in the air seemed to tell her that very few people ever came here."

    old "Xan waved his hand, bringing a light to the vault."
    new "Xan waved his hand, bringing a light to the vault."

    old "To Sarah's surprise, the light reached far and deeper into the darkness, but she could not make out the other end, so large was the vault."
    new "To Sarah's surprise, the light reached far and deeper into the darkness, but she could not make out the other end, so large was the vault."

    old "Everywhere she looked, she could see an endless variation of treasure. Trinkets, gold, jewels, paintings."
    new "Everywhere she looked, she could see an endless variation of treasure. Trinkets, gold, jewels, paintings."

    old "The wealth of an empire was on display here, or whatever was left of one."
    new "The wealth of an empire was on display here, or whatever was left of one."

    old "Now what? What are we looking for?"
    new "Now what? What are we looking for?"

    old "We'll split up, the vault is far too large."
    new "We'll split up, the vault is far too large."

    old "We're looking for a stone, a shining red jewel."
    new "We're looking for a stone, a shining red jewel."

    old "Like a ruby?"
    new "Like a ruby?"

    old "Not quite a ruby, but something like it. You'll know it when you see it. It emits a sort of crimson red light."
    new "Not quite a ruby, but something like it. You'll know it when you see it. It emits a sort of crimson red light."

    old "When you find it, no matter what, do not touch it."
    new "When you find it, no matter what, do not touch it."

    old "Call me over, and I will handle it from there."
    new "Call me over, and I will handle it from there."

    old "Because it's beyond dangerous, Sarah. It's more dangerous than you can possibly imagine, and I don't want you handling it."
    new "Because it's beyond dangerous, Sarah. It's more dangerous than you can possibly imagine, and I don't want you handling it."

    old "Fine, I'll call you over should I find it."
    new "Fine, I'll call you over should I find it."

    old "Good, I'll go left, you take right."
    new "Good, I'll go left, you take right."

    old "With that, Xan took off."
    new "With that, Xan took off."

    old "Once, artist and labourers poured their sweat and tears into creating these masterworks, all so they could end up here, forgotten."
    new "Once, artist and labourers poured their sweat and tears into creating these masterworks, all so they could end up here, forgotten."

    old "Sarah slowly followed her path, illuminating her path with a simple spell."
    new "Sarah slowly followed her path, illuminating her path with a simple spell."

    old "Sarah committed  the painting to mind. Then, she reached out, and with the touch of her palm, burned it."
    new "Sarah committed  the painting to mind. Then, she reached out, and with the touch of her palm, burned it."

    old "The old material of the canvas caused it to catch fire easily, burning out in only a few seconds. Like that, it was gone. Remaining only to Sarah's own mind."
    new "The old material of the canvas caused it to catch fire easily, burning out in only a few seconds. Like that, it was gone. Remaining only to Sarah's own mind."

    old "It was as Xan had said a stone that shone with light of crimson, but it was also not quite a gemstone or a ruby."
    new "It was as Xan had said a stone that shone with light of crimson, but it was also not quite a gemstone or a ruby."

    old "She tried to remind herself, because the object seemed to almost reach out to her, begging to be seized."
    new "She tried to remind herself, because the object seemed to almost reach out to her, begging to be seized."

    old "Acting before she could finish her thought, her hand had reached out and grabbed the object."
    new "Acting before she could finish her thought, her hand had reached out and grabbed the object."

    old "Sarah nearly turned to call out to Xan, only for the light around her to begin to fade."
    new "Sarah nearly turned to call out to Xan, only for the light around her to begin to fade."

    old "Something arose from the shadow, swirling and shifting. One most familiar to Sarah."
    new "Something arose from the shadow, swirling and shifting. One most familiar to Sarah."

    old "No way to greet an old friend, Sarah."
    new "No way to greet an old friend, Sarah."

    old "Is that what we are? Friends?"
    new "Is that what we are? Friends?"

    old "The spirit spun and twirled around the stone."
    new "The spirit spun and twirled around the stone."

    old "Sarah was unsure of what this meant. The spirit had always been bound in place by its flask. For it to now move so freely, here of all places..."
    new "Sarah was unsure of what this meant. The spirit had always been bound in place by its flask. For it to now move so freely, here of all places..."

    old "How are you appearing here?"
    new "How are you appearing here?"

    old "Here...there..."
    new "Here...there..."

    old "Not all concepts that govern your species are quite so strict on mine."
    new "Not all concepts that govern your species are quite so strict on mine."

    old "The space around this stone is as near to me as the flask, and as near as some other places. It is you that has moved far, I have sat still."
    new "The space around this stone is as near to me as the flask, and as near as some other places. It is you that has moved far, I have sat still."

    old "I've come all this way, just to be tortured by your riddles?"
    new "I've come all this way, just to be tortured by your riddles?"

    old "Why, were you hoping we could do something else?"
    new "Why, were you hoping we could do something else?"

    old "The spirit taunted her with their carnal connection."
    new "The spirit taunted her with their carnal connection."

    old "Don't flatter yourself. You're a tool to an end."
    new "Don't flatter yourself. You're a tool to an end."

    old "A hiss emerged from the spirit, what passed for laughter."
    new "A hiss emerged from the spirit, what passed for laughter."

    old "Sarah hated herself for allowing the creature to seize her body, yet knew she could not deny her weakness for it."
    new "Sarah hated herself for allowing the creature to seize her body, yet knew she could not deny her weakness for it."

    old "The spirit was silent."
    new "The spirit was silent."

    old "Tell me, why are you appearing here?"
    new "Tell me, why are you appearing here?"

    old "I told you a long time ago, Sarah, that there were things we could speak of, but only when the time was right."
    new "I told you a long time ago, Sarah, that there were things we could speak of, but only when the time was right."

    old "That moment is now, in this place..."
    new "That moment is now, in this place..."

    old "Sarah observed the spirit. Its intentions, much like its shape, were hard to grasp."
    new "Sarah observed the spirit. Its intentions, much like its shape, were hard to grasp."

    old "Because here we can speak freely."
    new "Because here we can speak freely."

    old "And we couldn't in Xan's house?"
    new "And we couldn't in Xan's house?"

    old "We couldn't anywhere, Sarah. Always eyes, always ears, everywhere, watching, looking, seeing. Only in this space are we unseen."
    new "We couldn't anywhere, Sarah. Always eyes, always ears, everywhere, watching, looking, seeing. Only in this space are we unseen."

    old "Unseen?"
    new "Unseen?"

    old "The creature twisted through the air."
    new "The creature twisted through the air."

    old "Here, so near the stone, the gods can't see us."
    new "Here, so near the stone, the gods can't see us."

    old "The gods..."
    new "The gods..."

    old "What are you talking about? Enought with the riddles!"
    new "What are you talking about? Enought with the riddles!"

    old "Sarah stomped her feet on the ground."
    new "Sarah stomped her feet on the ground."

    old "The gods of your world have long vanished, so many have forgotten they ever existed. But they have only lain dormant."
    new "The gods of your world have long vanished, so many have forgotten they ever existed. But they have only lain dormant."

    old "They hide in the place beyond, observing the passing of this world."
    new "They hide in the place beyond, observing the passing of this world."

    old "Sarah shook her head. As always, the spirit enjoyed obscuring his meaning."
    new "Sarah shook her head. As always, the spirit enjoyed obscuring his meaning."

    old "What are you talking about? The gods are a story we tell, they're not real."
    new "What are you talking about? The gods are a story we tell, they're not real."

    old "Ooh no, sweet Sarah, they are far more than fiction."
    new "Ooh no, sweet Sarah, they are far more than fiction."

    old "The mage told you of the empire that preceded all other empires. Of how an empress made a foul bargain, and cursed my world to be fixed under yours."
    new "The mage told you of the empire that preceded all other empires. Of how an empress made a foul bargain, and cursed my world to be fixed under yours."

    old "Sarah remembered that story."
    new "Sarah remembered that story."

    old "After, the gods of your world vanished, but in truth, they merely escaped it. They hid because the destruction caused by the world collision killed one of them and left the others weakened."
    new "After, the gods of your world vanished, but in truth, they merely escaped it. They hid because the destruction caused by the world collision killed one of them and left the others weakened."

    old "For the first time in their existence, they realized they could die."
    new "For the first time in their existence, they realized they could die."

    old "Fearing their own deaths, they escaped."
    new "Fearing their own deaths, they escaped."

    old "But not before enacting their final scheme, the Golden Path."
    new "But not before enacting their final scheme, the Golden Path."

    old "Sarah observed the creature. It had no face, and with it, no hints as to whether it spoke truth or lie."
    new "Sarah observed the creature. It had no face, and with it, no hints as to whether it spoke truth or lie."

    old "The Golden Path?"
    new "The Golden Path?"

    old "Your gods weaved fate itself into the fabric of your world. They uttered their design, and created the mechanism by which to manifest it."
    new "Your gods weaved fate itself into the fabric of your world. They uttered their design, and created the mechanism by which to manifest it."

    old "They both saw the future, and uttered it into existence, at the same time."
    new "They both saw the future, and uttered it into existence, at the same time."

    old "Sarah rubbed her temples in frustration."
    new "Sarah rubbed her temples in frustration."

    old "It means that your race, as well as mine, was forever trapped. Trapped to walk down a road that only led to one outcome."
    new "It means that your race, as well as mine, was forever trapped. Trapped to walk down a road that only led to one outcome."

    old "Their victory. Their return. The resumption of divinity."
    new "Their victory. Their return. The resumption of divinity."

    old "All the world and all its people dream themselves free, but in truth, walk in the divine plan of your gods, robbed of their agency."
    new "All the world and all its people dream themselves free, but in truth, walk in the divine plan of your gods, robbed of their agency."

    old "Each unkowingly performs the inevitable act that will bring about their rebirth."
    new "Each unkowingly performs the inevitable act that will bring about their rebirth."

    old "Sarah struggled to make sense of what the spirit was telling her."
    new "Sarah struggled to make sense of what the spirit was telling her."

    old "All the world a fiction, each soul playing a pre-written part in some play, authored by another."
    new "All the world a fiction, each soul playing a pre-written part in some play, authored by another."

    old "Then...all our lives...are already determined?"
    new "Then...all our lives...are already determined?"

    old "The spirit shifted, excited."
    new "The spirit shifted, excited."

    old "No, Sarah, not all lives..."
    new "No, Sarah, not all lives..."

    old "The gods can see everything, they know everything."
    new "The gods can see everything, they know everything."

    old "Rising up against them is foolishness, for they have forseen every resistance, and will prevent any that might rise, and those that do, they willed to occur. Everything walks in their path."
    new "Rising up against them is foolishness, for they have forseen every resistance, and will prevent any that might rise, and those that do, they willed to occur. Everything walks in their path."

    old "This stone..."
    new "This stone..."

    old "The spirit weaved its body around it."
    new "The spirit weaved its body around it."

    old "These are rare artifacts, called fate stones."
    new "These are rare artifacts, called fate stones."

    old "We pulled them, deep from void of the underworld, as a means of fighting back."
    new "We pulled them, deep from void of the underworld, as a means of fighting back."

    old "They block the sight of the gods, making them blind to what transpires near the stone."
    new "They block the sight of the gods, making them blind to what transpires near the stone."

    old "This is why you could never tell me this before...because in Xan's house, the gods would have seen and heard us..."
    new "This is why you could never tell me this before...because in Xan's house, the gods would have seen and heard us..."

    old "The spirit hissed."
    new "The spirit hissed."

    old "Yes, Sarah, that's right. Had I spoken back then, they would have known, and our resistance would have been futile from the start."
    new "Yes, Sarah, that's right. Had I spoken back then, they would have known, and our resistance would have been futile from the start."

    old "Resistance?"
    new "Resistance?"

    old "Yes, together, Sarah, we can resist this tyranny of heaven. Break free from the chains of your gods, and return agency to the world."
    new "Yes, together, Sarah, we can resist this tyranny of heaven. Break free from the chains of your gods, and return agency to the world."

    old "The control they wield over this world is but a fraction of what they will wield if they return."
    new "The control they wield over this world is but a fraction of what they will wield if they return."

    old "All the world will become theirs, down to every atom. If they are reborn, their yoke will become unbreakable."
    new "All the world will become theirs, down to every atom. If they are reborn, their yoke will become unbreakable."

